==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Civil Service Commission
<hw>Civil Service Commission</hw>. <def>In the United States, a
commission appointed by the President, consisting of three members, not
more than two of whom may be adherents of the same party, which has the
control, through examinations, of appointments and promotions in the
classified civil service. It was created by act of Jan, 16, 1883 (22
Stat. 403).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Civil Service Reform</ent>⟦br⟧
